mally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel De Bolbec was born about 1180. She married Robert De Vere from 1208 to 1219. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 3 February 1245, at the age of 66."},"et":{"ABT 1180–3 FEB 1245":"umbes 1180–3. veebruar 1245","1124–1221":"1124–1221","1218–1274":"1218–1274","1180–1245":"1180–1245","25 OCT 1221":"25. oktoober 1221","3 FEB 1245":"3. veebruar 1245","1245":"1245","1124":"1124","1221":"1221","1274":"1274","BET 1208 AND 1219":"1208 kuni 1219","ABT 1180":"umbes 1180","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Bakewell, Derbyshire, England":"Bakewell, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1180–3 FEB 1245":"noin 1180–3. helmikuuta 1245","1124–1221":"1124–1221","1218–1274":"1218–1274","1180–1245":"1180–1245","25 OCT 1221":"25. lokakuuta 1221","3 FEB 1245":"3. helmikuuta 1245","1245":"1245","1124":"1124","1221":"1221","1274":"1274","BET 1208 AND 1219":"vuodesta 1208 vuoteen 1219","ABT 1180":"noin 1180","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Bakewell, Derbyshire, England":"Bakewell, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"ABT 1180–3 FEB 1245":"environ 1180–3 février 1245","1124–1221":"1124–1221","1218–1274":"1218–1274","1180–1245":"1180–1245","25 OCT 1221":"25 octobre 1221","3 FEB 1245":"3 février 1245","1245":"1245","1124":"1124","1221":"1221","1274":"1274","BET 1208 AND 1219":"du 1208 au 1219","ABT 1180":"environ 1180","1218":"1218","1180":"1180","Bakewell, Derbyshire, England":"Bakewell, Derbyshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Isabel De Bolbec est née environ 1180. Elle a épousé Robert De Vere du 1208 au 1219. Ils ont eu